  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Account Strategist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Client Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Act as the main point of contact for assigned client accounts</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain strong, long-term client relationships</p></li><li><p>Lead client meetings, calls, and presentations</p></li><li><p>Understand client goals, challenges, and KPIs</p></li><li><p>Manage expectations and ensure high levels of client satisfaction</p></li></ul><p><strong>Account Growth (Upsell & Cross-Sell)</strong></p><ul><li><p>Identify opportunities to upsell existing services and cross-sell new offerings</p></li><li><p>Proactively recommend solutions that align with client needs and business goals</p></li><li><p>Prepare proposals, estimates, and scope documents for additional work</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with sales and leadership teams on account growth strategies</p></li></ul><p><strong>Project & Internal Coordination</strong></p><ul><li><p>Translate client requirements into clear briefs for internal teams</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with creative, marketing, media, and/or technical teams to ensure timely delivery</p></li><li><p>Monitor timelines, budgets, and scope to prevent overruns</p></li><li><p>Flag risks early and help resolve issues before they escalate</p></li></ul><p><strong>Reporting & Performance</strong></p><ul><li><p>Track account performance and project progress</p></li><li><p>Prepare and present reports, updates, and results to clients</p></li><li><p>Use data and insights to inform recommendations and renewals</p></li></ul>",
